header.gameNote: DRAKE REGENCY CHALLENGE AT DES MOINES IA

article.headline: Troy 84, Northern Illinois 81
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- O'Darien Bassett scored a game-high 20 points and Troy beat Northern Illinois 84-81 Saturday to claim third place in the Drake Regency Classic. The Trojans (5-5) withstood a furious comeback by the Huskies, who whittled a 19-point hole early in the second half into a 73-72 deficit with 6:10 left. Three field goals by Quintan Lipkins and two by Egan Grafel sparked a 19-3 run by Northern Illinois (3-4). A 3-pointer by Cedric Jackson and a jumper by Richard Chaney gave Troy a five-point cushion and the Trojans forced two crucial turnovers in the final minute to secure the win. Mike McKinney led the Huskies with 19 points and James Hughes added 16. Chaney finished with 18 points and Jackson had 14 for the Trojans.
